  "type": "mcq",
  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">The dimensions of a right rectangular prism are 4&nbsp;inches by 5&nbsp;inches by 6&nbsp;inches. What is the surface area, in square inches, of the prism?</p>\n",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">30</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">74</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">120</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">148</p>\n"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. The surface area is found by summing the area of each face. A right rectangular prism consists of three pairs of congruent rectangles, so the surface area is found by multiplying the areas of three adjacent rectangles by 2 and adding these products. For this prism, the surface area is equal to <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 times, open parenthesis, 4 times 5, close parenthesis, plus, 2 times, open parenthesis, 5 times 6, close parenthesis, plus, 2 times, open parenthesis, 4 times 6, close parenthesis\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 times 20, plus, 2 times 30, plus, 2 times 24\"></span>, which is equal to 148.<p>Choice A is incorrect. This is the area of one of the faces of the prism. Choice B is incorrect and may result from adding the areas of three adjacent rectangles without multiplying by 2. Choice C is incorrect. This is the volume, in cubic inches, of the prism.</p></p>\n",
